            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-surface-100 mb-1">Should Technology Replace Teachers in Schools?</h2>
            <p class="text-xs text-surface-500 mb-4">Prompt: Some people believe that technology will eventually replace teachers in schools. To what extent do you agree or disagree? Give reasons and include relevant examples.</p>
            <div class="bg-surface-900 rounded-xl p-5 border border-surface-700 text-surface-300 leading-relaxed text-sm space-y-3">
                <p>In recent years, the rapid development of technology has led some people to argue that teachers may eventually become unnecessary in schools. While I acknowledge the growing role of technology in education, I strongly disagree that it can fully replace teachers.</p>
                <p>There are several reasons why technology can be a valuable educational tool. Online platforms and AI-powered applications can personalise learning, allowing students to study at their own pace. For example, programmes like Khan Academy provide instant feedback and adapt exercises to a student's level, something that would be impossible in a large classroom. Furthermore, digital resources give students access to a vast amount of information that was previously unavailable in rural or underfunded schools.</p>
                <p>However, technology cannot replicate the human dimensions of teaching. A skilled teacher does not merely deliver information; they inspire curiosity, build relationships, and respond to the emotional needs of their students. Children, especially at a young age, require human interaction to develop social skills and emotional intelligence. Moreover, teachers can identify when a student is struggling not because of academic difficulty, but because of personal problems at home — something no algorithm can detect.</p>
                <p>In conclusion, while technology is an incredibly powerful supplement to education, it cannot and should not replace teachers entirely. The most effective educational model is one where technology and skilled teachers work together, each enhancing the other's strengths.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-3 text-xs text-surface-500">
                <span class="flex items-center gap-1"><svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5 text-amber-400" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path d="M9.049 2.927c.3-.921 1.603-.921 1.902 0l1.07 3.292a1 1 0 00.95.69h3.462c.969 0 1.371 1.24.588 1.81l-2.8 2.034a1 1 0 00-.364 1.118l1.07 3.292c.3.921-.755 1.688-1.54 1.118l-2.8-2.034a1 1 0 00-1.175 0l-2.8 2.034c-.784.57-1.838-.197-1.539-1.118l1.07-3.292a1 1 0 00-.364-1.118L2.98 8.72c-.783-.57-.38-1.81.588-1.81h3.461a1 1 0 00.951-.69l1.07-3.292z"/></svg> Clear position, logical structure, good vocabulary, some repetition</span>
            </div>
        </div>

        {{-- ── Task 2 Band 9 ── --}}
